This paper deals with the application of Independent Component Analysis (ICA) techniques for speckle noise reduction in Optical Coherence Tomography (OCT) images of the retina. This involves image processing and signal analysis, which are typically covered in the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Information Theory (cs.IT), Multimedia (cs.MM), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories of arXiv CS. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
